<paragraph id="8BD936C0FFE9FFD2FF23FDCACD59FDDD" blockId="1.[151,623,546,572]" box="[151,623,546,572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="D09181ACFFE9FFD2FF23FDCACD59FDDD" bold="true" box="[151,623,546,572]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FF23FDCACD59FDDD" bold="true" box="[151,623,546,572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FF7BFDCACE89FDDD" box="[207,447,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FF7BFDCACE89FDDD" bold="true" box="[207,447,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Pegomya terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD936C0FFE9FFD2FF23FD82CD3AFB85" blockId="1.[151,1437,618,2004]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FF23FD82CE67FD65" author="Griffiths" box="[151,337,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2, 161 - 288. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1983">
Griffiths (
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FEBFFD82CE7EFD65" box="[267,328,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
defined a 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FE79FD82CD8EFD62" box="[461,696,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FE79FD82CD8EFD62" box="[461,696,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Pegomya terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superspecies in which he identified 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FBD1FD82CB42FD65" box="[1125,1140,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
Nearctic and 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FAADFD82CA11FD65" box="[1305,1319,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
Holarctic species. The monophyly of this species group was strongly supported by a peculiar elongation of the distal part of the phallus (e.g., 
<figureCitation id="135D2A45FFE9FFD2FE0BFD52CD21FD35" box="[447,535,698,724]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="8.[151,269,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[205,1394,319,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,278,1961]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Pegomya terminalis, male. 16, 17. Sternite V, ventral and lateral views. 18, 19. Hypopygium, caudal and lateral views. 20. Pre- and postgonites, lateral view. 21. Phallus and phallapodeme in lateral view, ejaculatory apodeme in oblique ventral view. Same scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274304/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FE42FD52CD21FD35" box="[502,535,698,724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). However, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FD62FD52CCF5FD32" box="[726,963,698,723]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FD62FD52CCF5FD32" box="[726,963,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Pegomya terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group as defined in the present paper even includes a species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FDB7FD0ACC2BFD1D" authority="Ackland" authorityName="Ackland" box="[515,797,738,764]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FDB7FD0ACD99FD1A" box="[515,687,738,763]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. granadensis</emphasis>
Ackland
</taxonomicName>
, without the elongation of the distal phallus (
<figureCitation id="135D2A45FFE9FFD2FA82FD0ACABBFD1D" box="[1334,1421,738,764]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1363,208,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,208,1988]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Pegomya granadensis, male. 8, 9. Sternite V, ventral and lateral views. 10, 11. Hypopygium, caudal and lateral views. 12. Pre- and postgonites, lateral view. 13. Phallus, lateral view. Same scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274302/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FAD9FD0ACABBFD1D" box="[1389,1421,738,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). The argument for grouping 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FE69FCE2CDBFFCC2" box="[477,649,778,803]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FE69FCE2CDBFFCC2" box="[477,649,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. granadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FC81FCE2CCFFFCC2" box="[821,969,778,803]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FC81FCE2CCFFFCC2" box="[821,969,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and allied species is the obvious agreement in a number of apomorphic traits in the female abdomen and oviscapt (see 
<figureCitation id="135D2A45FFE9FFD2FBDBFCDACBC9FCAD" box="[1135,1279,818,844]" captionStart="FIGURES 14, 15" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1435,1459]" captionTargetBox="[186,1379,338,1434]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,314,1449]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14, 15. Pegomya granadensis, female. 14. Oviscapt, flat mounted. 15. Distal part of same." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274303/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
Figs. 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FB07FCDACBC9FCAD" box="[1203,1279,818,844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="14.15">14, 15</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="135D2A45FFE9FFD2FA8AFCDACAB9FCAD" box="[1342,1423,818,844]" captionStart="FIGURES 22, 23" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,783,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[156,1430,749,1878]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 22, 23. Pegomya terminalis, female. 22. Oviscapt, flat mounted. 23. Distal part of same." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FA8AFCDACAB9FCAD" box="[1342,1423,818,844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="22.23">22, 23</number>
</figureCitation>
): length of tergite V tends to exceed combined length of tergites III and IV; fully extended oviscapt with very long “intersegmental” membranes and 1.5–2.0x as long as remaining abdomen, portion distal to segment VI increasingly depressed; segment VI short, but abundantly setose at hind margins of weakly sclerotized tergite and sternite; segments VII and VIII very long, with numerous fine to very reduced setulae at hind margins; epiproct more or less reduced, with 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FD8BFC12CD5DFBF5" box="[575,619,1018,1044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="0.0">0–3</number>
apical setulae; hypoproct small, with scattered setulae and no cuticular pubescence; cerci depressed, only bearing short setulae and sensilla, towards apex forming a cutting edge (less evident in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FEFBFBA3CECDFB85" box="[335,507,1099,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FEFBFBA3CECDFB85" box="[335,507,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. granadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C654BFFE9FFD2FF72FB9ACB31F865" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BD936C0FFE9FFD2FF72FB9ACBA6FA2D" blockId="1.[151,1437,618,2004]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FF48FB9BCEDEFB6D" box="[252,488,1139,1164]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FF48FB9BCEDEFB6D" box="[252,488,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Pegomya terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is presently known by five species endemic to the Nearctic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FAD4FB9ACE24FB55" author="Griffiths" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2, 161 - 288. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1983">
Griffiths 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FF66FB72CE24FB55" box="[210,274,1178,1204]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): 
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FE92FB73CEBBFB55" box="[294,397,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. g l a b r a</emphasis>
(Stein, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FE58FB72CD1DFB55" box="[492,555,1178,1204]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1920.0">1920</number>
), 
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FD8BFB73CD83FB55" box="[575,693,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. d i s t i c h a</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FD74FB72CC46FB55" author="Griffiths" box="[704,880,1178,1204]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2, 161 - 288. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1983">
Griffiths, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FC87FB72CC46FB55" box="[819,880,1178,1204]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FCC8FB73CBE2FB55" authority="Griffiths, 1983" authorityName="Griffiths" authorityYear="1983" box="[892,1236,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviventris">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FCC8FB73CB2BFB55" box="[892,1053,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. flaviventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FB90FB72CBE2FB55" author="Griffiths" box="[1060,1236,1178,1204]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2, 161 - 288. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1983">
Griffiths, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FB23FB72CBE2FB55" box="[1175,1236,1178,1204]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FB54FB73CE22FB3D" authority="Griffiths, 1983" authorityName="Griffiths" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aldrichi">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FB54FB73CA6CFB55" box="[1248,1370,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. aldrichi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FAD5FB72CE22FB3D" author="Griffiths" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2, 161 - 288. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1983">
Griffiths, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FF6DFB2ACE22FB3D" box="[217,276,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FEF8FB2BCD47FB3D" authority="Huckett, 1939" authorityName="Huckett" authorityYear="1939" box="[332,625,1218,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedrica">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FEF8FB2BCEF7FB3D" box="[332,449,1219,1244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. cedrica</emphasis>
Huckett, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FD87FB2ACD47FB3D" box="[563,625,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</taxonomicName>
. A further species recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F3717650FFE9FFD2FC4DFB2ACB67FB3D" box="[1017,1105,1218,1244]" name="Canada" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Canada</collectingCountry>
as ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FB35FB2BCAA1FB3D" authority="Rondani" authorityName="Rondani" box="[1153,1431,1218,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FB35FB2BCA22FB3D" box="[1153,1300,1219,1244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. terminalis</emphasis>
(Rondani)
</taxonomicName>
’ by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FF09FB02CE44FAE5" author="Griffiths" box="[189,370,1258,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1983) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 2, 161 - 288. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1983">
Griffiths (
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FE80FB02CE44FAE5" box="[308,370,1258,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1983.1997">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FE34FB02CE8AFAE5" author="Griffiths" box="[384,444,1258,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1997) Anthomyiid flies (Diptera: Anthomyiidae) of the Yukon. In: Danks, H. V. &amp; Downes, J. A. (Eds.), Insects of the Yukon. Biological Survey of Canada (Terrestrial Arthropods), Ottawa, pp. 687 - 722." type="book chapter" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
) appears to be new. From the West Palaearctic subregion are presently known five species, of which four are largely Mediterranean: 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FCB5FAFBCB5DFACD" authority="Rondani, 1866" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1866" box="[769,1131,1298,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FCB5FAFBCCACFACD" box="[769,922,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. terminalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FC1AFAFACB55FACD" author="Rondani" box="[942,1123,1298,1324]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Rondani, C. (1866) Anthomyinae Italicae, collectae distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 9, 68 - 217." type="journal article" year="1866">
Rondani, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FB93FAFACB55FACD" box="[1063,1123,1298,1324]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1866.0">1866</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
ranging from 
<collectingCountry id="F3717650FFE9FFD2FA97FAFACA50FACD" box="[1315,1382,1298,1324]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Spain</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3717650FFE9FFD2FF23FAD2CE37FAB5" box="[151,257,1338,1364]" name="Morocco" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Morocco</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3717650FFE9FFD2FE9BFAD2CE80FAB5" box="[303,438,1338,1364]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D43FFE9FFD2FE71FAD3CC05FAB5" authority="Ackland, 1977" authorityName="Ackland" authorityYear="1977" box="[453,819,1338,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis id="B912EAD2FFE9FFD2FE71FAD3CD40FAB5" box="[453,630,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">P. granadensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B31FFE9FFD2FD36FAD2CC05FAB5" author="Ackland" box="[642,819,1338,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Ackland, D. M. (1977) Some Anthomyiidae from Southern Spain, with descriptions of two new species (Insecta, Diptera). Steenstrupia, 4, 195 - 209." type="journal article" year="1977">
Ackland, 
<number id="3DAE24E7FFE9FFD2FD4CFAD2CC05FAB5" box="[760,819,1338,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</bibRefCitation>
